juniDosProtectionPlatformMIB.name: juniDosProtectionPlatformMIB

revisions.description: Added dos-protection-group support and added MAC address to flow traps.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniDosProtectionPlatformMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniDosProtectionPlatformMIB.description: The DOS Protection MIB for the Juniper E-Series product family. This MIB contains managed objects for the DOS Protection application, which are platform specific. Management objects are provided to control and monitor the DOS protection application.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolTable.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolTable
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolTable.description: The information for the DOS protection control protocols for a specific slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolEntry.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolEntry
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolEntry.description: The information for an individual control protocol on a specific slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolSlot.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolSlot
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolSlot.description: The slot value for the entry.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolIndex.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolIndex
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolIndex.description: The control protocol value for the entry.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolState.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolState
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolState.description: The current state of the protocol. This object will return inTrouble(2) if the specific slot referenced is reporting that the protocol is currently being watched for suspicious flows. If the module is not reporting that this protocol is being watched this object will return ok(1). A protocol is in trouble for a slot when the sum of the rate of all flows for the protocol is over the limit for that protocol.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolTransi.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolTransitions
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotProtocolTransi.description: The number of transitions to 'inTrouble' that this control protocol has made for this slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowEntry.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowEntry
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowEntry.description: Information about a suspicious control flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowSlot.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowSlot
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowSlot.description: The slot value for the flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowIfIndex.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowIfIndex
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the flow. For group flows, this value will be zero.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowGroupId.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowGroupId
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowGroupId.description: The group id for the flow. The group id will be zero for an individual flow. It is non-zero when the entry represents a group of flows.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowProtocol.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowProtocol
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowProtocol.description: The control protocol for the flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowRate.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowRate
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowRate.description: The current rate in packets per second for the flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowPeakRate.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowPeakRate
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowPeakRate.description: The peak rate in packets per second for the flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowTimeFlagge.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowTimeFlagged
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowTimeFlagge.description: The sysUpTime value for the time when the flow was determined to be suspicious.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowIngressSlo.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowIngressSlot
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowIngressSlo.description: For control flow that are monitored on the egress processor in the forwarding path, this value will indicate the possible ingress slot for data stream that is possibly causing this suspicious flow control. This object will report -1 when it is undefined

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowGroup.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowGroup
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowGroup.description: Indicates whether the flow is a group flow or not. A value of true(1) indicates that the flow represents a group of flows. A value of false(2) indicates that the flow is an individual flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowClearEntry.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowClearEntry
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowClearEntry.description: When set to clear(1), the suspicious control flow is removed from the suspicious control flow table. When set to ok(0), there is no effect and the suspicious control flow is unchanged. When read, always returns a value of ok(0).

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacEntry.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacEntry
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacEntry.description: Information about a suspicious control flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacSlot.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacSlot
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacSlot.description: The slot value for the flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacIfIndex.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacIfIndex
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the flow. For group flows, this value will be zero.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacGroupId.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacGroupId
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacGroupId.description: The group id for the flow. The group id will be zero for an individual flow. It is non-zero when the entry represents a group of flows.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacProtoco.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacProtocol
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacProtoco.description: The control protocol for the flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacSrcMac.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacSrcMac
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacSrcMac.description: The source MAC address for the flow. A null source MAC address indicates that no source physical address was available.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacRate.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacRate
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacRate.description: The current rate in packets per second for the flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacPeakRat.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacPeakRate
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacPeakRat.description: The peak rate in packets per second for the flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacTimeFla.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacTimeFlagged
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacTimeFla.description: The sysUpTime value for the time when the flow was determined to be suspicious.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacIngress.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacIngressSlot
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacIngress.description: For control flow that are monitored on the egress processor in the forwarding path, this value will indicate the possible ingress slot for data stream that is possibly causing this suspicious flow control. This object will report -1 when it is undefined

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacGroup.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacGroup
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacGroup.description: Indicates whether the flow is a group flow or not. A value of true(1) indicates that the flow represents a group of flows. A value of false(0) indicates that the flow is an individual flow.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacClearEn.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacClearEntry
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotFlowMacClearEn.description: When set to clear(1), the suspicious control flow is removed from the suspicious control flow table. When set to ok(0), there is no effect and the suspicious control flow is unchanged. When read, always returns a value of ok(0).

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotTable.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotTable
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotTable.description: The suspicious control flow information for each slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotEntry.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotEntry
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotEntry.description: The information for a specific slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotSlot.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotSlot
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotSlot.description: The slot value for this entry.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotClearAll.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotClearAll
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotClearAll.description: When set to clear(1), the suspicious control flow detection system is cleared for this slot. When set to ok(0), there is no effect and the suspicious control flow detection system is unchanged. By clearing the suspicious control flow detection system all flows on the slot are removed from the suspicious flow table. When read, always returns a value of ok(0).

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotDiscontinuityT.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotDiscontinuityTime
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotDiscontinuityT.description: The sysUpTime at which the counters were re-adjusted due to slot restart.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotTableOverflowS.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotTableOverflowState
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotTableOverflowS.description: Indicates whether this slot is under a resource shortage situation. A value of notOverflowingOrGrouping(1) indicates that there is no resource shortage on the slot. A value of grouping(2) or overflowing(3) indicates that this module is suffering from a resource shortage and has acted according to the state of the juniDosProtectionScfdsGlobalGrouping object.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotCurrentSuspici.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotCurrentSuspiciousFlows
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotCurrentSuspici.description: The number of flows currently marked as suspicious for this slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotNumberSuspicio.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotNumberSuspiciousFlows
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotNumberSuspicio.description: The number of suspicious flows seen on this slot, since slot restart

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotNumberSuspicio.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotNumberSuspiciousFlowGroups
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotNumberSuspicio.description: The number of suspicius flow groups seen on this slot since slot restart.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotCurrentSuspici.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotCurrentSuspiciousFlowGroups
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotCurrentSuspici.description: The number of flows currently falsely considered suspicious for this slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotCurrentFalseNe.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotCurrentFalseNegativeFlows
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotCurrentFalseNe.description: The number of flows currently falsely considered suspicious on this slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotNumberFalseNeg.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotNumberFalseNegativeFlows
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotNumberFalseNeg.description: The number of suspicious flows seen on this slot, since this slot restart.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotOverflows.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotOverflows
juniDosProtectionScfdsSlotOverflows.description: The number of times this slot has had a table overflow.

juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateTable.name: juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateTable
juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateTable.description: This table provides information about the calculated minimum rates (as well as the maximum rates) for each dos-protection-group control protocol for each line module.

juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateEntry.name: juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateEntry
juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateEntry.description: The rates for an individual dos-protection-group on an line module for a control protocol.

juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateSlot.name: juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateSlot
juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateSlot.description: The slot value for this entry.

juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateDpgName.name: juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateDpgName
juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateDpgName.description: The dos-protection-group name for this entry.

juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateProtocol.name: juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateProtocol
juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateProtocol.description: The control protocol for this entry.

juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMinRate.name: juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMinRate
juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMinRate.description: The minimum rate for this control protocol on this slot for this dos-protection-group. This value is calculated based on the priority rate and oversubscription as well as the control protocol weight

juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMaxRate.name: juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMaxRate
juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMaxRate.description: The maximum rate for this protocol on this slot for this dos-protection-group. This is equivalent to the configured rate for the dos-protection-group

juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMinBurst.name: juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMinBurst
juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMinBurst.description: The minimum burst for this control protocol on this slot for this dos-protection-group. This value is calculated based on the priority burst and oversubscription as well as the control protocol weight

juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMaxBurst.name: juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMaxBurst
juniDosProtectionDpgSlotRateMaxBurst.description: The maximum burst for this protocol on this slot for this dos-protection-group. This is equivalent to the configured burst for the dos-protection-group

juniDosProtectionScfdsFlowRate.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsFlowRate
juniDosProtectionScfdsFlowRate.description: The flow rate at the creation time.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousControlF.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousControlFlow
juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousControlF.description: This trap will be generated when a control flow becomes suspicious.

juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousContr.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousControlFlow
juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousContr.description: This trap will be generated when a control flow becomes no longer suspicious

juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousControlF.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousControlFlowGroup
juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousControlF.description: This trap will be generated when a control flow that represents a group becomes suspicious.

juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousContr.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousControlFlowGroup
juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousContr.description: This trap will be generated when a control flow that represents a group becomes no longer suspicious.

juniDosProtectionScfdsTableFull.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsTableFull
juniDosProtectionScfdsTableFull.description: This trap will be generated when the suspicious flow control table becomes full on a slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsTableNotFull.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsTableNotFull
juniDosProtectionScfdsTableNotFull.description: This trap will be generated when the suspicious flow control table is no longer full on a slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsGroupingInUse.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsGroupingInUse
juniDosProtectionScfdsGroupingInUse.description: This trap will be generated when the suspicious flow control system begins to group flow controls on a slot, due to the suspicious flow control table being full.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousProtocol.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousProtocol
juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousProtocol.description: This trap will be generated when a control protocol becomes suspicious on a slot, and therefore the suspicious control flow system begins to watch flows of this control protocol type.

juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousProto.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousProtocol
juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousProto.description: This trap will be generated when a control protocol becomes no longer suspicious on a slot, and therefore the suspicious control flow system will no longer watch flows of this control protocol type.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousPriority.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousPriority
juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousPriority.description: This trap will be generated when a control priority becomes suspicious on a slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousPrior.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousPriority
juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousPrior.description: This trap will be generated when a control priority becomes no longer suspicious on a slot.

juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousControlF.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousControlFlowMac
juniDosProtectionScfdsSuspiciousControlF.description: This trap will be generated when a control flow becomes suspicious.

juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousContr.name: juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousControlFlowMac
juniDosProtectionScfdsNonSuspiciousContr.description: This trap will be generated when a control flow becomes no longer suspicious

juniDosProtectionCompliance.name: juniDosProtectionCompliance
juniDosProtectionCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper Dos Protection Platform specific MIB. Obsoleted with the addition of dos-protection groups.

juniDosProtectionCompliance2.name: juniDosProtectionCompliance2
juniDosProtectionCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper Dos Protection Platform specific MIB.

juniDosProtectionGroup.name: juniDosProtectionGroup
juniDosProtectionGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of platform specific aspects of the DOS protection application in a Juniper product. This became obsolete with the addition of MAC address in the flow table and the addition of dos-protection-groups.

juniDosProtectionNotificationGroup.name: juniDosProtectionNotificationGroup
juniDosProtectionNotificationGroup.description: Collection of objects for DOS protection application notifications in a Juniper product.This became obsolete with the addition of MAC address in flow traps.

juniDosProtectionGroup1.name: juniDosProtectionGroup1
juniDosProtectionGroup1.description: A collection of objects providing management of platform specific aspects of the DOS protection application in a Juniper product.

juniDosProtectionNotificationGroup1.name: juniDosProtectionNotificationGroup1
juniDosProtectionNotificationGroup1.description: Collection of objects for DOS protection application notifications in a Juniper product.
